The paper involves a game with a surveillance requirement and a secondary objective to maximize visibility, which suggests it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of a convolutional neural network for approximating information gain suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves decision-making and optimization, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
